## Appendix B: Tool Architecture

### Schema Builder Tool Components

```
src/schema_builder/
├── __init__.py
├── contract_to_ddl.py          # Main CLI script
├── parser.py                   # JSON Schema parser
├── type_mapper.py              # JSON Schema → Delta type mapping
├── ddl_generator.py            # DDL template rendering
├── uc_metadata.py              # UC tags, comments, ownership
├── templates/
│   ├── table.sql.j2            # Table DDL template
│   └── constraint.sql.j2       # Constraint template
└── utils.py                    # Utilities

generated/ddl/
├── 01_engagement.sql
├── 02_work_package.sql
└── ... (31 total)

tests/schema_builder/
├── test_parser.py
├── test_type_mapper.py
├── test_ddl_generator.py
├── test_table_conformance.py  # Main validation suite
└── test_integration.py
```

### CLI Usage

```bash
# Generate DDL for all contracts
python -m schema_builder.contract_to_ddl \
  --input-dir contracts/ \
  --output-dir generated/ddl/ \
  --catalog main \
  --schema source_discovery

# Generate DDL for single contract
python -m schema_builder.contract_to_ddl \
  --input contracts/engagement.schema.json \
  --output generated/ddl/engagement.sql \
  --catalog main \
  --schema source_discovery

# Execute DDL (create tables)
python -m schema_builder.contract_to_ddl \
  --input-dir contracts/ \
  --catalog main \
  --schema source_discovery \
  --execute

# Validate tables against contracts
pytest tests/schema_builder/test_table_conformance.py -v
```

